<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 3:27PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Davidson, northwestern Montgomery and Stanly Counties through 415 PM
EDT...
At 327 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mt Pleasant, or 7 miles east of Downtown Concord, moving northeast at
20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Badin Lake, Plyler, Midland, High Rock Lake, Locust,
Badin, Oakboro, Denton and Stanfield.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
